<doc id="3435" url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=3435" title="String Quartet No. 16 (Beethoven)">
String Quartet No. 16 (Beethoven)

The String Quartet No. 16 in F major, Op. 135, by Ludwig van Beethoven was written in October 1826 and was the last major work he completed. Only the final movement of the Quartet Op. 130, written as a replacement for the "GroÃŸe Fuge", was composed later. The op. 135 quartet was premiered by the Schuppanzigh Quartet in March 1828, one year after Beethoven's death. 

The work is on a smaller scale than the other late quartets. Under the introductory slow chords in the last movement Beethoven wrote in the manuscript ""MuÃŸ es sein?"" (Must it be?) to which he responds, with the faster main theme of the movement, ""Es muÃŸ sein!"" (It must be!). The whole movement is headed ""Der schwer gefaÃŸte EntschluÃŸ"" ("The Difficult Decision").

It is in four movements:
The performance of the work takes around 22â€“25 minutes.



